sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant Django as Django (web)
    participant CeleryWorker as Celery Worker
    participant PipelineRunner
    participant PrefectBackend
    participant PrefectServer as Prefect Server
    participant PrefectWorker as Prefect Worker
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    participant S3

    User->>Django: POST /flows/upload-and-process/
    Django->>DB: FlowExecution.create(status=PENDING)
    Django->>CeleryWorker: run_pipeline_task.delay(flow_run_id, input_s3_path)
    Django-->>User: 302 → execution detail page

    CeleryWorker->>PipelineRunner: run_pipeline(run_id, input_s3_path)
    Note over PipelineRunner: settings.PIPELINE_BACKEND == "prefect"
    PipelineRunner->>PrefectBackend: run(execution)

    PrefectBackend->>PrefectServer: POST /api/deployments/{id}/create_flow_run
    PrefectServer-->>PrefectBackend: {id: "<prefect-flow-run-uuid>"}
    PrefectBackend->>DB: FlowExecution.external_run_id = "<prefect-flow-run-uuid>"

    loop Poll every 2 s until terminal state
        PrefectBackend->>PrefectServer: GET /api/flow_runs/<prefect-flow-run-uuid>
        PrefectServer-->>PrefectBackend: {state: {type: "RUNNING"|"COMPLETED"|"FAILED"}}
    end

    Note over PrefectWorker: Worker picks up flow run from work pool

    loop Each pipeline step (01_ingest → 02_validate → 03_transform → 04_aggregate)
        PrefectWorker->>PrefectServer: Claim task run
        PrefectWorker->>Django: POST /internal/step-status/ {status: "RUNNING", …} [Bearer token]
        Django->>DB: ExecutionStep.status = RUNNING, started_at = now()

        PrefectWorker->>S3: Read input Parquet (previous step output)
        PrefectWorker->>PrefectWorker: papermill.execute_notebook(step_name, params)
        PrefectWorker->>S3: Write output Parquet + result.json (final step only)

        alt Step succeeds
            PrefectWorker->>Django: POST /internal/step-status/ {status: "COMPLETED", …}
            Django->>DB: ExecutionStep.status = COMPLETED, completed_at = now()
        else Step fails
            PrefectWorker->>Django: POST /internal/step-status/ {status: "FAILED", error_message: …}
            Django->>DB: ExecutionStep.status = FAILED, error_message = …
        end
    end

    PrefectServer-->>PrefectBackend: state.type == "COMPLETED"
    PrefectBackend->>S3: Read result.json
    S3-->>PrefectBackend: {row_count, s3_output_path, …}
    PrefectBackend-->>PipelineRunner: metadata dict
    PipelineRunner-->>CeleryWorker: metadata dict

    CeleryWorker->>DB: FlowExecution.status = COMPLETED, row_count, s3_output_path

    Note over User,Django: User polls execution_live_status (HTMX)\nand sees steps update in real time via POST /internal/step-status/ callbacks

    opt User cancels (RUNNING execution)
        User->>Django: POST /flows/execution/<run_id>/stop/
        Django->>PrefectServer: DELETE /api/flow_runs/<prefect-flow-run-uuid>/cancel
        Django->>DB: FlowExecution.status = FAILED, error_message = "Stopped by user."
        Django-->>User: 302 → execution detail
    end
